1
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,920
Then give me my plan back!

2
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:46,880
<i>Get down. And what do you need money for</i>

3
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:48,920
when you're holding my heart
in your hands?

4
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,280
I'm giving you my whole body and heart.
Still not enough?

5
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,920
Enough. Stop.

6
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:58,760
<i>Please don't overlook my efforts again.</i>

7
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,920
Do you two hug like this a lot?

8
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,960
<i>When you signed the contract with me,</i>
<i>didn't you read the clause</i>

9
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:05,760
forbidding work with competitors?

10
00:03:05,840 --> 00:03:08,520
Pakbung didn't come to help me
as an employee.

11
00:03:08,600 --> 00:03:10,080
- She came because--
- I needed money.

12
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:13,720
You think I'm the reason Mr. Trai
will lose to Mr. Rachen, right?

13
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:16,560
Because Trai's weakness is love.

14
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,040
<i>You are his weakness.</i>

15
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:21,160
Should I step away from you, Mr. Trai?

16
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,040
Are you going to take everything from me?!

17
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,400
- You took things from me too.
- Me? I took things from you?!

18
00:03:25,480 --> 00:03:26,520
Yeah! Starting with Dad.

19
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,240
Because you were a screw-up!

20
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:41,000
We closed the new applicant count
at 10:00 a.m.,

21
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:42,640
before this meeting began,

22
00:03:42,720 --> 00:03:46,000
and here are the final results
for both Mr. Trai and Mr. Rachen.

23
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:49,520
COMPETITION RESULTS FOR THE CEO POSITION

24
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:52,760
Mr. Rachen is ahead of Mr. Trai by 3.4%.

25
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,080
Mr. Rachen wins.

26
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,760
How is that possible?

27
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,600
I checked this morning,
and Mr. Trai was still leading.

28
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:04,280
You can lead and still lose.

29
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:06,360
What are you gonna do about it?

30
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:11,280
Excuse me, may I check the list in detail?

31
00:04:11,880 --> 00:04:14,920
Why? You think we cheated or something?

32
00:04:16,800 --> 00:04:18,800
- Did you know?
- Know what?

33
00:04:19,440 --> 00:04:22,160
You should accept defeat
with dignity, Mr. Trai.

34
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:25,480
And did you win with dignity?

35
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:28,960
Hey! Are you saying my mom cheated?

36
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:30,880
Hey, I'm just asking.

37
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:32,680
Why are you upset?

38
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,920
Does anyone here
think these results aren't normal?

39
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:48,400
The result is what it is.
We have to respect the rules, Trai.

40
00:04:49,680 --> 00:04:52,960
Then I'd like to congratulate
the next CEO.

41
00:05:05,400 --> 00:05:07,640
Trai, why are you giving up so easily?

42
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
Congratulations, Rachen.

43
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,000
You haven't even started,
and you're acting arrogant.

44
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,920
Shake my hand.

45
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:34,080
You gave in too easily.

46
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:38,080
I told you. I don't want the position.

47
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,360
I want two things.

48
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,760
Don't abandon the customers in my project.

49
00:05:51,760 --> 00:05:53,080
And don't forget Dad's intention.

50
00:05:57,520 --> 00:05:58,520
I'm counting on you.

51
00:06:19,080 --> 00:06:21,640
Mrs. Mookmanee, was that your doing?

52
00:06:24,400 --> 00:06:26,960
If you knew you didn't win
on your own merit,

53
00:06:27,720 --> 00:06:29,280
why didn't you object in the meeting?

54
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:31,680
You really rigged the competition.

55
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:34,240
Even though you didn't beg me,

56
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,280
Mom still showed mercy and helped you.

57
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,560
You should be thanking her.

58
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:38,880
But I never asked.

59
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,120
Then go tell everyone.

60
00:06:40,200 --> 00:06:41,880
Tell them that you actually lost.

61
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:45,600
Go ahead and tell them

62
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:49,600
you don't want the CEO position.
Give it back to him.

63
00:06:50,440 --> 00:06:51,320
Go.

64
00:06:54,040 --> 00:06:57,200
If what I did humiliates your ego so much,

65
00:06:57,280 --> 00:06:59,480
if it ruins your honor that badly,

66
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,600
then deny the role.

67
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:03,640
But if you can't,

68
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,080
then you have to repay me.

69
00:07:07,200 --> 00:07:09,120
Because I'm the only one

70
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,960
who can give you what you want.

71
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:27,760
Mr. Trai.

72
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,320
Pakbung?

73
00:07:32,640 --> 00:07:34,800
I was delivering something nearby.

74
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,520
Are you okay?

75
00:07:38,960 --> 00:07:39,800
Not really.

76
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,840
Come on. Not being CEO today
isn't the end of the world.

77
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,520
You can try again.

78
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,040
Anyway, are you hungry?

79
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:51,720
Wanna eat something? Wanna do something?

80
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,160
Go somewhere?

81
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:56,520
I want to ride around.

82
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:59,080
Ride around?

83
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,880
I don't look crazy, right?

84
00:08:41,159 --> 00:08:42,919
Crazy? You're super cute.

85
00:09:11,800 --> 00:09:13,480
Uh, you can sit here.

86
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,800
If you can't reach, you can hold onto me.

87
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:31,680
Here.

88
00:09:33,760 --> 00:09:34,960
Oh.

89
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:38,040
Who's the one who needs to hold on?

90
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,760
Hold on.

91
00:09:42,880 --> 00:09:43,880
Why?

92
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,080
You think I can't reach?

93
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,600
So you're not actually upset.

94
00:10:17,760 --> 00:10:20,120
Just a bit. Not much.

95
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,560
And besides, I didn't even lose.

96
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,800
But you didn't get the position.

97
00:10:30,480 --> 00:10:31,600
Was it because of me?

98
00:10:34,200 --> 00:10:35,560
The numbers were weird.

99
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,240
I think someone manipulated something.

100
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,080
You mean

101
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:42,720
someone cheated?

102
00:10:43,800 --> 00:10:44,640
Yeah.

103
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:46,840
Mr. Rachen?

104
00:10:48,800 --> 00:10:50,520
I don't think Rachen knows about it.

105
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:53,080
The one behind it
is probably Mrs. Mookmanee.

106
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:57,480
Only rotten people can do rotten things.

107
00:10:58,320 --> 00:10:59,680
You have to find evidence

108
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:01,320
and expose them.

109
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,240
I will.

110
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:05,320
But I'm waiting.

111
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,200
Waiting for what?

112
00:11:07,960 --> 00:11:10,560
I want to see how Rachen handles this.

113
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:36,880
If this is what you wanted,
then smile and accept it.

114
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,280
Thank you all for your support.

115
00:11:51,880 --> 00:11:57,000
I promise I will be committed
and develop--

116
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,960
So Be Rich
can generate more profit than ever before,

117
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:04,680
for the benefit of all Be Rich employees.

118
00:12:35,240 --> 00:12:37,240
And for the greatest benefit of Be Rich,

119
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:41,200
I've decided that I will…

120
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,600
Marry Mika.

121
00:12:55,760 --> 00:12:58,680
The three of us, as one family,

122
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:02,080
will push Be Rich
to become number one in Asia.

123
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:18,640
We never talked about a wedding.

124
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,680
You shouldn't force this on me like this.

125
00:13:20,760 --> 00:13:22,880
Don't you care about the damage
to your daughter?

126
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,160
What damage?

127
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,720
You're the only one who will
suffer damage by not marrying her.

128
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:30,360
Mika, you want to marry me?

129
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,800
Do you really love me?

130
00:13:34,400 --> 00:13:35,520
Rachen,

131
00:13:35,600 --> 00:13:38,880
people at our level don't marry
because they love each other.

132
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,840
They marry because it benefits both sides.

133
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:44,800
Right, Mom?

134
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,200
Have you thought about it?

135
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:54,640
How will you, an orphan with no roots,

136
00:13:55,280 --> 00:13:58,520
stripped of your father's influence,
keep living in this society?

137
00:13:59,600 --> 00:14:02,160
You're capable, but you have no backing.

138
00:14:03,280 --> 00:14:05,680
At best, you'll be a department head.

139
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,600
You'll never reach the executive level.

140
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:10,600
Yes.

141
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,160
I'm your special pass,

142
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:16,120
your VIP card, your fast track.

143
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:18,000
How can you still not get it?

144
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:20,680
Do you want Mom to cancel this deal

145
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:22,800
and let you go back to being a nobody?

146
00:14:23,480 --> 00:14:24,720
Is that what you want?

147
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:31,000
I've never given anyone this much before.

148
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,440
One bowl of vermicelli noodles
with meatballs, stewed beef, no liver.

149
00:14:53,520 --> 00:14:55,680
A consolation prize for the loser.

150
00:14:55,760 --> 00:14:58,800
Go on. Dig in. My treat.

151
00:14:59,400 --> 00:15:01,360
I told you I didn't lose.

152
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,680
Pennywort juice.

153
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,640
For internal bruising.

154
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:12,600
- I didn't--
- Leave the trash behind.

155
00:15:12,680 --> 00:15:14,080
Don't be trash.

156
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,080
I mean, don't give up.

157
00:15:17,160 --> 00:15:18,560
One day,

158
00:15:18,640 --> 00:15:20,240
it will be our day.

159
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,160
Fine. Sure.

160
00:15:26,240 --> 00:15:28,800
At first, I didn't think I'd lose either,
but…

161
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:32,680
Come on.
If you have more ways to comfort me,

162
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:34,080
bring it on.

163
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:37,480
Here. I'm giving you an extra bowl.

164
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:39,760
Eat a lot.

165
00:15:39,840 --> 00:15:42,520
So you'll have the energy to cry.

166
00:15:49,360 --> 00:15:50,520
So you really want me to eat?

167
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,440
Yeah, eat.

168
00:15:54,040 --> 00:15:55,000
Good.

169
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,160
I've been wanting
to eat pakbung for a long time.

170
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,520
Mr. Trai!

171
00:16:03,280 --> 00:16:04,480
Are you crazy?

172
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,200
What's with the dirty mind right now?

173
00:16:06,280 --> 00:16:08,840
I mean this pakbung. Morning glory.

174
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:11,120
What are you thinking?
Your mind's so dirty.

175
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,880
Oh, blushing, huh?

176
00:16:19,960 --> 00:16:22,280
I know what you're thinking.
Red cheeks and flaring nostrils.

177
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:24,480
I'm wearing blush, okay?

178
00:16:25,760 --> 00:16:27,680
See? I'm eating pakbung too.

179
00:16:32,680 --> 00:16:33,840
This is only the beginning.

180
00:16:34,440 --> 00:16:37,040
Mrs. Mookmanee is already trying
to control everything you do.

181
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:38,240
It'll get worse from here.

182
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:41,080
Today, she gave you something,

183
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:44,120
but she'll want
a hundred times back in return.

184
00:16:44,200 --> 00:16:47,640
She's treating you
like a piece on her board.

185
00:16:47,720 --> 00:16:49,480
Now that you're CEO,

186
00:16:49,560 --> 00:16:51,720
you don't need her anymore.

187
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,680
Do you think Dad can see me?

188
00:17:17,920 --> 00:17:20,000
I'm going to make Be Rich
greater than ever.

189
00:17:22,319 --> 00:17:23,800
No matter where you are,

190
00:17:25,560 --> 00:17:27,480
you have to look down and see me…

191
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:30,760
see my love.

192
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:46,440
I think I'm going back
to building the school.

193
00:17:47,760 --> 00:17:51,000
An alternative school where students
are the center of everything.

194
00:17:51,080 --> 00:17:52,800
Do you want to be an executive?

195
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:56,120
Running a school?

196
00:17:56,200 --> 00:17:58,200
Study a bit more. I think you can do it.

197
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:03,120
Interesting.

198
00:18:05,120 --> 00:18:06,160
But…

199
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,200
you'll have a salary for me, right?

200
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,400
Are you happy right now?

201
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,880
- How's that relevant?
- Come on. Answer me.

202
00:18:18,960 --> 00:18:20,280
Are you happy right now?

203
00:18:23,040 --> 00:18:24,240
I'm not sad.

204
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,680
So I guess I'm happy.

205
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,240
There's research, you know.

206
00:18:30,320 --> 00:18:33,920
They've studied it for hundreds of years.
They say happiness

207
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:37,400
doesn't depend on money or career success.

208
00:18:37,920 --> 00:18:39,720
It depends on the relationship

209
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,040
between yourself
and the people around you.

210
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:47,200
If I became CEO today

211
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:49,960
but didn't have you or anyone else,

212
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:53,560
I wouldn't be smiling like this.

213
00:18:56,600 --> 00:18:57,840
That might be true.

214
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,400
So if you're with me,

215
00:19:04,480 --> 00:19:05,560
you don't need money anymore, right?

216
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:06,640
Hey.

217
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,400
No way. I need money.

218
00:19:11,760 --> 00:19:14,040
So, between me and money,

219
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,360
which do you choose?

220
00:19:20,360 --> 00:19:21,600
You. Money.

221
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,840
Both.

222
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:27,600
Both?

223
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:45,200
Are you sure stepping back
is going to make you happy?

224
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,880
I just don't want you to regret it later.

225
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,440
Even if I don't step back,

226
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,400
there's no place for me anymore.

227
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:56,800
I did my best, Rut.

228
00:19:56,880 --> 00:20:00,360
But if Trai won't do anything
when he knows he was cheated,

229
00:20:00,440 --> 00:20:01,880
then I really can't do anything.

230
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:04,560
Even though we tried too,

231
00:20:05,160 --> 00:20:06,800
maybe even more than him.

232
00:20:06,880 --> 00:20:10,560
So why do we have no right
to choose anything at all?

233
00:20:11,640 --> 00:20:12,920
Because we don't have money.

234
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:16,160
Money can buy everything,

235
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:19,600
even human worth.

236
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:24,040
I won't accept that.
I'll help you myself, Ms. Darin.

237
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:26,800
I won't let you be pushed down,
be overlooked.

238
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,840
You'll go back to Be Rich.

239
00:20:28,920 --> 00:20:31,280
You'll get back everything
that belongs to you.

240
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:47,240
I won't let your money be worth
more than anyone's life ever again.

241
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:05,840
Trai?

242
00:21:10,840 --> 00:21:11,680
Darin?

243
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:18,880
Who's that?

244
00:21:21,520 --> 00:21:22,720
I'm asking. Who's that?

245
00:21:29,040 --> 00:21:30,000
It's me, sir.

246
00:21:31,120 --> 00:21:33,200
I came to bring documents to Mr. Rachen.

247
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:35,000
Rachen sent you?

248
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:38,560
Yes, sir. Mr. Rachen told me
to come get these documents.

249
00:21:38,640 --> 00:21:39,760
No.

250
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,880
I mean what you did to my son.

251
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,760
So the private investigator
reported everything to you.

252
00:22:01,480 --> 00:22:03,920
- Why?
- You really don't know?

253
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:06,680
Look at my face.

254
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:09,960
Do I look familiar?

255
00:22:11,960 --> 00:22:14,240
Everyone says
I look exactly like my father.

256
00:22:17,840 --> 00:22:20,280
You forgot the man who had
to go to jail in your son's place?

257
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:22,240
You're Rat's son?

258
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:24,560
Yes. He's my dad.

259
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:25,880
Your driver.

260
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,720
The man who admitted he drove that car.

261
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,720
My dad lived in your house,

262
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:32,360
served you from morning till night.

263
00:22:33,120 --> 00:22:34,600
And every time he called home,

264
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:36,640
all he ever said

265
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:39,080
was how capable you were,
how rich you were.

266
00:22:39,160 --> 00:22:41,360
He admired you. He worshipped you.

267
00:22:41,960 --> 00:22:43,680
But you used him,

268
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:45,960
made him take the fall
for your rotten son.

269
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:51,880
You think I used him?

270
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:55,040
Because you don't know the truth.

271
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,840
Your father

272
00:22:57,520 --> 00:23:00,120
didn't do it out of love or worship.

273
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:01,360
He did it

274
00:23:01,880 --> 00:23:03,240
because he wanted money.

275
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:06,360
He offered it himself.

276
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:09,000
He said he'd take responsibility
in exchange for 5 million.

277
00:23:09,080 --> 00:23:10,240
Bullshit.

278
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:13,040
Why would my dad go to jail for just that?

279
00:23:13,120 --> 00:23:14,840
"Just" that?

280
00:23:14,920 --> 00:23:16,000
It was 5 million.

281
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:18,600
It made your family happy.
It gave you comfort.

282
00:23:18,680 --> 00:23:20,480
Happy, my ass.

283
00:23:21,080 --> 00:23:23,360
Don't you know
your money destroyed my family?

284
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:26,120
Relatives fought each other
because of your money.

285
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:30,000
My mother got stabbed to death
by her brother because of your money!

286
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:32,800
- Give it to me. I must have some too.
- No.

287
00:23:32,880 --> 00:23:34,360
Give me that money.

288
00:23:34,440 --> 00:23:36,000
Uncle Wong, what are you doing to Mom?

289
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:38,920
- Wong, that's your nephew!
- Get out of the way, Rut!

290
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:41,160
That's your nephew.

291
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:43,000
Mom!

292
00:23:43,080 --> 00:23:44,120
- Mom!
- Stop!

293
00:23:44,200 --> 00:23:45,560
Mom.

294
00:23:46,240 --> 00:23:49,000
Mom… No…

295
00:23:51,840 --> 00:23:55,800
Mom, stay with me… Mom…
Please stay with me…

296
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,720
Mom…

297
00:23:57,800 --> 00:23:59,320
Mom…

298
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,800
And my dad…

299
00:24:01,400 --> 00:24:02,480
When he found out,

300
00:24:03,320 --> 00:24:05,760
he got sick and wasted away.
In the end, he died in prison.

301
00:24:05,840 --> 00:24:08,160
Everything got destroyed
because of your filthy money.

302
00:24:16,240 --> 00:24:17,480
I never knew about that.

303
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:19,480
I'm telling you now, aren't I?

304
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:23,480
Alright.

305
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:26,600
What do you want?

306
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:31,120
You sent threats,

307
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:33,280
tried to kill my son.

308
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:35,640
Why?

309
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,920
You want me to feel loss

310
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,360
the same way you did?

311
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,880
Yes. You people have to be ruined
the same way you ruined me.

312
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,440
Even if you kill me,

313
00:24:47,040 --> 00:24:49,160
you'll never feel better.

314
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,600
You know why?

315
00:24:52,360 --> 00:24:54,040
Because you love playing the victim.

316
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:58,000
You want to feel loss, pain, to be hurt,

317
00:24:58,600 --> 00:25:00,000
so you can blame others.

318
00:25:00,600 --> 00:25:02,320
But if you think properly,

319
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,520
you'll know that

320
00:25:04,600 --> 00:25:07,400
your family didn't fall apart
because of my money.

321
00:25:07,480 --> 00:25:09,680
It fell apart because of the greed
of those around you.

322
00:25:09,760 --> 00:25:10,680
Shut up!

323
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,640
I'm not a victim.
And I'll be the one to judge you.

324
00:25:14,320 --> 00:25:16,240
If I hadn't created
that anti-Be Rich page,

325
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:17,840
I'd never have known

326
00:25:19,200 --> 00:25:21,520
it wasn't just me who suffered
because of your money.

327
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:23,800
Your customers, hundreds,
thousands of them,

328
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:27,240
drowned in debt, lost everything,
had their lives destroyed.

329
00:25:27,320 --> 00:25:28,600
You've ruined so many people.

330
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,840
I won't let you die easily.

331
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:38,880
I want to see the day your sons
fight each other over your inheritance.

332
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:42,280
I want you to suffer
until the day Be Rich collapses.

333
00:25:43,600 --> 00:25:44,480
TRAI

334
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:45,600
Hey!

335
00:25:52,320 --> 00:25:53,400
You know too much.

336
00:25:53,480 --> 00:25:55,120
I can't let you live.

337
00:25:55,720 --> 00:25:57,240
Even if you destroy Be Rich,

338
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,400
the world will never change.

339
00:25:59,480 --> 00:26:03,080
Inequality will remain
because people will never be equal.

340
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,720
Everyone takes advantage
of others just to survive.

341
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,960
If you want justice,

342
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:09,600
then you have to be rich.

343
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:11,080
You have to have power as much as I do.

344
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:14,680
Death can make people equal too.

345
00:26:29,920 --> 00:26:31,440
Haven't you ever heard of this?

346
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:34,480
"Wealth means nothing when death arrives."

347
00:26:34,560 --> 00:26:35,880
‪Do you get it now?

348
00:26:42,800 --> 00:26:44,280
Your money

349
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:46,280
destroyed my family, Tritot.

350
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:55,080
Your sons will tear each other apart.

351
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:58,480
I'll destroy your family
with your own money.

352
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,360
Gambling online again?

353
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:17,680
Well.

354
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:21,520
Well…

355
00:27:22,120 --> 00:27:24,400
Well, I…

356
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:26,880
I… I had money left

357
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:30,320
on the site, like hundreds of thousands,

358
00:27:30,400 --> 00:27:32,600
so I was just trying to withdraw it.

359
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:34,760
Looks like I've treated you too well.

360
00:27:38,040 --> 00:27:39,000
Hey, hey, wait.

361
00:27:39,080 --> 00:27:41,200
Eak! What are you doing?

362
00:27:41,280 --> 00:27:42,800
I hate gambling addicts the most.

363
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:44,640
If you can't quit, then get out.

364
00:27:44,720 --> 00:27:46,280
Mrs. Mook.

365
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:47,880
Eak, let me go.

366
00:27:48,480 --> 00:27:51,080
Mrs. Mook, I'm sorry.

367
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:53,600
I was wrong.
I won't do it again, Mrs. Mook.

368
00:27:54,240 --> 00:27:56,560
I only give chances to people
who are useful to me.

369
00:27:58,200 --> 00:27:59,040
Are you?

370
00:28:04,560 --> 00:28:06,480
Waldorf teaching

371
00:28:06,560 --> 00:28:09,200
focuses on a holistic education,

372
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:11,920
so children develop learning processes

373
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,360
and live in harmony with nature.

374
00:28:21,320 --> 00:28:22,600
Honestly…

375
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:25,400
I'm already confused just by reading this.

376
00:28:25,480 --> 00:28:27,720
You really want me
to help you manage this?

377
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:29,800
Then are you ready to learn?

378
00:28:30,680 --> 00:28:32,000
I can learn…

379
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:37,320
but will you pay me to learn?

380
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:40,640
So you need money to be motivated?

381
00:28:41,280 --> 00:28:45,320
No money, no energy.

382
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,960
Then can I pay you with…

383
00:28:55,960 --> 00:28:56,880
love?

384
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,080
Mr. Trai.

385
00:28:59,160 --> 00:29:01,680
I already told you not to joke like that.

386
00:29:04,760 --> 00:29:06,280
Then read. Here.

387
00:29:06,360 --> 00:29:07,360
SAMLEE SENT A PHOTO

388
00:29:10,440 --> 00:29:11,920
What did Samlee send?

389
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:22,760
Back then, Mom had to go
on tour trips for long periods.

390
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:25,920
I didn't know
where to take the two of you,

391
00:29:26,560 --> 00:29:29,040
so I brought you here every evening.

392
00:29:32,560 --> 00:29:34,280
You put me on your shoulders,

393
00:29:35,320 --> 00:29:36,800
and I stuffed the ball into the hoop.

394
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:39,080
Kanah.

395
00:29:39,680 --> 00:29:40,720
You remember now, right?

396
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:44,520
See? I told you that
I really did raise you two.

397
00:29:44,600 --> 00:29:46,560
Back then, you were so cool.

398
00:29:47,320 --> 00:29:48,960
Sports, music, you could do everything.

399
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:50,840
Hey,

400
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:53,040
I'm still cool now.

401
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:57,600
So, what sports do you play?

402
00:30:01,680 --> 00:30:02,760
Can you play basketball?

403
00:30:06,120 --> 00:30:07,560
Just a sec.

404
00:30:07,640 --> 00:30:09,360
Excuse me.
Can I borrow the ball for a moment?

405
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:11,000
- Sure.
- Thank you.

406
00:30:13,160 --> 00:30:14,480
Come on.

407
00:30:14,560 --> 00:30:16,800
I can't really play.

408
00:30:17,400 --> 00:30:18,760
Why can't you play?

409
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:19,840
Here.

410
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:22,800
I borrowed it already.
You can't just stand there shaking.

411
00:30:23,600 --> 00:30:25,160
Huh? Here.

412
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:28,760
Let's go. Go.

413
00:30:30,600 --> 00:30:32,280
If you don't move, I'll steal it.

414
00:30:38,680 --> 00:30:39,800
Come on.

415
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:48,880
Alright, try it.

416
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:51,960
- Good job.
- Yeah!

417
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,600
Good job. Good job.

418
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:56,000
- Come on. Yeah!
- Yeah!

419
00:30:56,080 --> 00:30:58,080
Ready? Aim carefully.

420
00:30:58,160 --> 00:30:59,400
One, two, three.

421
00:31:10,120 --> 00:31:11,080
Come on.

422
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,280
Here, Kanah.

423
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,320
- Hey!
- Hey!

424
00:31:18,400 --> 00:31:20,200
Hey! Good job.

425
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,680
Good job. Good job.

426
00:31:21,760 --> 00:31:22,880
Good job, my son.

427
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:26,440
Come on, Kanah. This way.

428
00:31:26,520 --> 00:31:28,480
- Uh, wait.
- Yut!

429
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:36,600
Your debt hasn't been paid off.

430
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:38,560
You have no right
to be hanging around here.

431
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:40,640
What, Mr. Song?

432
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:42,960
I already paid you 50,000 last time.

433
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,600
Plus what you took from Pakbung
still isn't enough?

434
00:31:45,680 --> 00:31:47,400
Pakbung didn't even pay

435
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,400
half the interest.

436
00:31:49,480 --> 00:31:50,920
You borrowed 500,000,

437
00:31:51,640 --> 00:31:52,760
half a million, you know?

438
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,440
Good thing I ran into you today.

439
00:31:55,040 --> 00:31:57,520
Today, I'm collecting more.

440
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:58,800
Understand?

441
00:31:58,880 --> 00:32:00,360
Give me the money.

442
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,960
You hear me?

443
00:32:02,040 --> 00:32:02,720
- Ow!
- Hey!

444
00:32:02,800 --> 00:32:05,040
- Kanah, run!
- Hey!

445
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:09,280
Hurry. Go.

446
00:32:11,640 --> 00:32:14,600
Hey, I'll give you 1,000.
Get me out of here.

447
00:32:17,040 --> 00:32:17,880
Wait, wait.

448
00:32:21,440 --> 00:32:24,640
Kanah. Kanah. Come on. Hurry up.

449
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,400
Kanah!

450
00:32:35,400 --> 00:32:36,240
Kanah.

451
00:32:36,840 --> 00:32:38,400
Kanah, how are you?

452
00:32:39,080 --> 00:32:40,320
Kanah. How are you?

453
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:42,080
- I'm okay.
- How are you?

454
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,000
I'm alright.

455
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,520
What the hell were you thinking?

456
00:32:48,040 --> 00:32:49,960
Were you trying to kill Kanah?

457
00:32:50,040 --> 00:32:51,520
- Huh?!
- Hey.

458
00:32:51,600 --> 00:32:52,560
Bung. Bung.

459
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:53,920
Calm down.

460
00:32:54,520 --> 00:32:55,880
He didn't do anything to me.

461
00:32:57,920 --> 00:32:59,120
Kanah.

462
00:32:59,200 --> 00:33:00,160
Kanah. Kanah.

463
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,280
Hey!

464
00:33:10,360 --> 00:33:11,360
Stop.

465
00:33:13,360 --> 00:33:14,200
You wanna die?

466
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,560
Next time,

467
00:33:19,640 --> 00:33:21,040
if you don't pay,

468
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:22,880
you're dead.

469
00:33:24,040 --> 00:33:25,040
Let's go.

470
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,280
Kanah.

471
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,160
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

472
00:33:33,760 --> 00:33:35,240
Did you take it in time?

473
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:38,520
You did, right?

474
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:40,920
Kanah, Kanah!

475
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:42,640
Are you okay?

476
00:33:42,720 --> 00:33:44,000
Get up.

477
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:48,920
<i>But he came back to help me.</i>

478
00:33:49,840 --> 00:33:51,440
If it weren't for him, I'd be screwed.

479
00:33:52,040 --> 00:33:53,520
But he took you to play basketball.

480
00:33:55,520 --> 00:33:56,640
Did you forget

481
00:33:56,720 --> 00:33:58,240
Kanah has asthma?

482
00:33:58,320 --> 00:34:00,200
He can't do heavy exercise.

483
00:34:03,480 --> 00:34:05,320
Uh, I…

484
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,280
I'm sorry.

485
00:34:09,360 --> 00:34:11,159
You can't remember

486
00:34:11,239 --> 00:34:12,760
even life-or-death stuff like this,

487
00:34:13,400 --> 00:34:15,719
and you still dare call yourself a father?

488
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:16,639
You're…

489
00:34:16,719 --> 00:34:19,320
Uh, Pakbung…

490
00:34:19,400 --> 00:34:21,360
I'm really sorry.

491
00:34:22,080 --> 00:34:24,679
I thought Kanah had gotten better already.

492
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:27,360
Gotten better?

493
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:29,480
This disease never goes away.

494
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:32,320
You just didn't care,
didn't pay attention.

495
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,960
You abandoned us,
and now you come back and hurt us?

496
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:38,280
Why?

497
00:34:39,080 --> 00:34:40,480
You can't stand seeing us happy?

498
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:42,800
This place isn't yours.

499
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:44,880
- Get out.
- Pakbung. Ow.

500
00:34:44,960 --> 00:34:46,239
- Go.
- Bung.

501
00:34:46,320 --> 00:34:48,840
- Pakbung, enough.
- Pakbung, it hurts.

502
00:34:49,440 --> 00:34:51,080
Stop acting.

503
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:54,159
Hey, he got beaten up.

504
00:34:54,239 --> 00:34:55,760
It probably really does hurt.

505
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:58,480
Good. He deserved it.

506
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,440
And don't you dare get near Kanah again.

507
00:35:01,320 --> 00:35:02,280
Otherwise,

508
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,080
you'll get worse than this.

509
00:35:04,160 --> 00:35:05,280
Go.

510
00:35:05,360 --> 00:35:06,640
I said get out!

511
00:35:06,720 --> 00:35:07,920
- Ow! Pakbung.
- Bung.

512
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,920
Bung, enough!

513
00:35:11,080 --> 00:35:12,880
I wanted to play basketball
with him myself.

514
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:14,440
I wanted to be with him myself.

515
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:19,480
Kanah.

516
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:21,840
I barely remember him.

517
00:35:22,600 --> 00:35:24,560
Everything I know, I learned from you,

518
00:35:25,160 --> 00:35:26,920
only what you wanted me to know.

519
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:29,840
But I want to know him.

520
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,400
I want to see for myself
what kind of person he is.

521
00:35:33,200 --> 00:35:35,200
Can you let me learn for myself?

522
00:35:36,360 --> 00:35:37,480
I'm begging you.

523
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,280
Don't block me.

524
00:35:40,760 --> 00:35:42,320
Don't force me.

525
00:35:42,960 --> 00:35:44,200
Please.

526
00:35:45,680 --> 00:35:47,280
Don't send Dad away yet, please.

527
00:35:48,560 --> 00:35:49,960
You called him Dad?

528
00:35:50,640 --> 00:35:52,400
He is our dad.

529
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:58,400
Please let me get to know my dad too.

530
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:06,680
Pakbung…

531
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,480
‪It's alright. It's alright.

532
00:36:48,480 --> 00:36:49,760
‪It's alright. You've done well.

533
00:37:06,360 --> 00:37:08,360
Rachen, does this one look good?

534
00:37:09,200 --> 00:37:10,200
Yeah, it's fine.

535
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,880
Aren't you even going to look up?

536
00:37:13,480 --> 00:37:14,320
Why even bring him?

537
00:37:14,400 --> 00:37:16,240
He's so damn boring.

538
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:21,920
This isn't work time.

539
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:23,320
But I'm briefing my team.

540
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:25,440
But I'm telling you
to pay attention to me.

541
00:37:28,600 --> 00:37:31,960
Okay.
Then you can stay here with your friends.

542
00:37:32,640 --> 00:37:35,440
Rachen. Rachen, stop right now.

543
00:37:40,840 --> 00:37:42,480
You have no right to order me around.

544
00:37:42,560 --> 00:37:43,960
I'm not ordering you.

545
00:37:44,040 --> 00:37:45,640
I'm just telling you
what you're supposed to do.

546
00:37:45,720 --> 00:37:49,320
When you're with me,
you have to pay attention to me.

547
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:51,680
But you also only pay attention
to what you like, don't you?

548
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:52,840
What do you mean by that?

549
00:37:54,800 --> 00:37:55,640
Rachen.

550
00:37:56,240 --> 00:37:59,800
You don't pay attention to me
because you don't like me, right?

551
00:38:00,400 --> 00:38:03,040
So who do you like then?
Do you like that rotten Pakbung?

552
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:04,920
Why do you even care?

553
00:38:05,000 --> 00:38:07,480
In the end, we're getting married
for the benefits anyway.

554
00:38:13,920 --> 00:38:15,440
Rachen!

555
00:38:18,560 --> 00:38:20,760
I tried so hard to protect Kanah,

556
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:24,560
but now he wants to be with him.

557
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,320
Did Kanah upset you?

558
00:38:32,560 --> 00:38:33,880
I'm scared…

559
00:38:38,280 --> 00:38:40,800
scared that if Kanah loves him

560
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:43,000
and he leaves us again,

561
00:38:44,720 --> 00:38:47,200
Kanah will get hurt just like I did.

562
00:38:48,840 --> 00:38:50,720
When you faced that,

563
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:52,960
you were still very young.

564
00:38:53,560 --> 00:38:56,160
It makes sense that it stuck with you.

565
00:38:57,800 --> 00:38:59,120
So you're going to say

566
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:01,080
Kanah is grown up now,

567
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:03,760
and I should let him decide for himself?

568
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,040
No.

569
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,480
I'm going to say you're amazing

570
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:10,280
for getting through that back then.

571
00:39:14,640 --> 00:39:17,480
You're so strong.
You don't have to be afraid anymore.

572
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:23,800
But even if Kanah ends up disappointed,

573
00:39:25,720 --> 00:39:27,880
I believe he'll get through it too.

574
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:34,800
Because he has you.

575
00:39:44,080 --> 00:39:45,520
But if you feel like

576
00:39:45,600 --> 00:39:47,160
you don't want to be strong anymore,

577
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:49,160
if you want to be vulnerable

578
00:39:49,880 --> 00:39:51,960
and rest for a bit,

579
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,640
you can lean on me.

580
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:56,440
I won't charge you.

581
00:39:57,840 --> 00:39:58,800
Alright?

582
00:40:18,640 --> 00:40:19,560
Did she pick up?

583
00:40:20,920 --> 00:40:22,520
She's not answering any calls.

584
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:28,400
- Bung.
- Huh?

585
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,320
Let's go.

586
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:34,000
Pakbung. Why didn't you answer my calls?

587
00:40:34,080 --> 00:40:35,440
Where did you go?

588
00:40:36,760 --> 00:40:37,760
Nearby.

589
00:40:38,560 --> 00:40:39,560
Pakbung,

590
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:41,680
I'm sorry.

591
00:40:41,760 --> 00:40:44,000
When I told you he got hurt,

592
00:40:44,080 --> 00:40:45,840
I wasn't taking his side.

593
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:48,760
I'm on your side.
I'm always cheering for you.

594
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:50,920
Please don't be mad at me.

595
00:40:53,360 --> 00:40:54,160
I'm not mad.

596
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:56,040
Really?

597
00:41:03,240 --> 00:41:04,160
Have you eaten yet?

598
00:41:08,600 --> 00:41:10,200
Go on.

599
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:18,560
Well, I was waiting for you.
How about pork BBQ?

600
00:41:19,240 --> 00:41:20,080
Sure.

601
00:41:22,640 --> 00:41:25,400
Then I'll order. I'll order.

602
00:41:25,480 --> 00:41:26,880
No, no, no.

603
00:41:26,960 --> 00:41:29,160
I'll do it. My treat.

604
00:41:32,360 --> 00:41:33,600
If you want to go,

605
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:35,440
you can go, Kanah.

606
00:41:35,520 --> 00:41:36,640
Go where?

607
00:41:36,720 --> 00:41:38,840
To get to know him,

608
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,640
the one you call "Dad".

609
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:43,040
I'm not going.

610
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:45,280
Huh? Didn't you say you wanted to?

611
00:41:45,960 --> 00:41:49,040
I said I wanted to know him.
I didn't say I wanted to go.

612
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:50,480
I'm not going anywhere.

613
00:41:50,560 --> 00:41:51,960
I'm staying with you.

614
00:41:52,560 --> 00:41:53,680
Fine.

615
00:41:54,560 --> 00:41:55,480
Stay then.

616
00:41:55,560 --> 00:41:57,480
Yeah. I'm staying. Right here.

617
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:59,240
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

618
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:02,320
Ouch! Bung.

619
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:04,520
It hurts. Ouch! Trai.

620
00:42:04,600 --> 00:42:07,560
Stop. Go away.

621
00:42:07,640 --> 00:42:09,480
Trai, look at her.

622
00:42:10,000 --> 00:42:11,600
Help me.

623
00:42:11,680 --> 00:42:13,480
I want to stay with you too.

624
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:15,880
Can I?

625
00:42:16,560 --> 00:42:18,840
Well, you're already staying, aren't you?

626
00:42:20,120 --> 00:42:23,040
Uh, wait.

627
00:42:23,120 --> 00:42:26,880
"Already staying" means
staying in the same house?

628
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,480
Or staying in your life?

629
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:34,200
In your heart?

630
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:38,480
If she's acting like this,
it means your flirting worked.

631
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:43,040
Pakbung has opened her heart.

632
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:46,400
Right? Hey!

633
00:42:46,480 --> 00:42:49,640
- You missed!
- You're blushing and turning violent.

634
00:42:49,720 --> 00:42:51,320
Oh, come on. Don't try to cover it up.

635
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:54,400
- Don't try to cover it up.
- What?

636
00:42:56,880 --> 00:42:58,640
Little grin.

637
00:42:59,240 --> 00:43:01,080
You want another 500,000?

638
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:03,480
Yes, Mrs. Mook.

639
00:43:04,040 --> 00:43:06,200
Please help me.

640
00:43:06,280 --> 00:43:09,800
It's nothing, just one of your handbags.

641
00:43:11,840 --> 00:43:16,720
Getting back together with your kids
is worth as much as one of my bags?

642
00:43:20,680 --> 00:43:23,320
Please help me.

643
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:26,120
If I don't have this money,

644
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:27,800
I can't go back to that house.

645
00:43:30,080 --> 00:43:31,320
Just give it to him.

646
00:43:34,200 --> 00:43:35,280
And after taking the money,

647
00:43:35,360 --> 00:43:37,800
go tell your daughter
to stop messing with Rachen.

648
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:40,960
Rachen still hasn't cut contact with her?

649
00:43:41,040 --> 00:43:44,160
No. And I'm not going
to tolerate it anymore.

650
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:47,200
I'll give you another 500,000,

651
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:51,040
but you must make Pakbung
disappear from Rachen's life.

652
00:43:51,120 --> 00:43:54,120
I don't want to see her face.
I don't even want to hear her name.

653
00:43:58,600 --> 00:44:01,640
Well, with enough money, I can do it.

654
00:44:01,720 --> 00:44:02,760
You'd better.

655
00:44:05,000 --> 00:44:06,360
But if you fail,

656
00:44:07,560 --> 00:44:09,800
I'll be the one who makes you
disappear from this world.

657
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:19,320
You look really happy
after going to Pakbung's place this time.

658
00:44:19,400 --> 00:44:20,480
Did something good happen?

659
00:44:20,560 --> 00:44:21,560
Secret.

660
00:44:22,640 --> 00:44:24,360
You're keeping things from us now?

661
00:44:24,960 --> 00:44:26,080
What about the thing I asked you to do?

662
00:44:26,160 --> 00:44:29,240
- All set. I had our people--
- Now that you're not Be Rich's CEO,

663
00:44:29,320 --> 00:44:31,120
you seem pretty relaxed.

664
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:34,720
Good timing, Da.

665
00:44:35,240 --> 00:44:38,400
I talked to a friend.
He owns an ad agency.

666
00:44:38,480 --> 00:44:40,880
Put together a portfolio and résumé.
I'll talk to him for you.

667
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:42,520
Are you dumping me?

668
00:44:43,160 --> 00:44:44,320
I thought you wanted to work.

669
00:44:44,400 --> 00:44:46,560
I want to work at Be Rich,

670
00:44:46,640 --> 00:44:47,840
with you as CEO.

671
00:44:47,920 --> 00:44:48,840
But I'm not the CEO.

672
00:44:48,920 --> 00:44:50,280
Because you were cheated.

673
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:55,240
Proof of how they cheated you.

674
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:04,360
LIST OF APPLICANTS
FOR THE BE RICH CASH APPLICATION

675
00:45:06,280 --> 00:45:07,120
I don't know.

676
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:10,680
Where did you get this?

677
00:45:11,320 --> 00:45:12,560
That doesn't matter.

678
00:45:12,640 --> 00:45:14,280
Just remember this.

679
00:45:14,360 --> 00:45:16,240
I'm willing to trade anything…

680
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:18,520
for you.

681
00:45:25,320 --> 00:45:27,320
I, SONG SAELEE, HAVE RECEIVED 500,000 BAHT
FROM MR. YONGYUT WAEWSAWANG

682
00:45:27,400 --> 00:45:29,360
I HEREBY CERTIFY THAT THE ABOVE
IS TRUE IN ALL RESPECTS.

683
00:45:29,440 --> 00:45:31,160
SONG SAELEE
CREDITOR

684
00:45:31,240 --> 00:45:32,480
YONGYUT WAEWSAWANG
DEBTOR

685
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:36,000
So Mr. Song agreed to sign this?

686
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:38,600
What, you don't believe it?

687
00:45:38,680 --> 00:45:41,040
I secretly recorded it too.

688
00:45:41,680 --> 00:45:42,800
Here.

689
00:45:43,320 --> 00:45:44,800
<i>Because of this money,</i>

690
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:46,520
I couldn't stay with my children,

691
00:45:47,040 --> 00:45:48,080
couldn't take care of them,

692
00:45:48,720 --> 00:45:50,360
and caused them trouble.

693
00:45:50,440 --> 00:45:52,960
I'm returning this money to you,

694
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:55,040
so my kids can finally stop hating me.

695
00:46:01,480 --> 00:46:05,600
I know it might be a little late.

696
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:07,120
But…

697
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:08,720
Pakbung,

698
00:46:10,280 --> 00:46:11,360
Kanah,

699
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:14,040
could you give me another chance?

700
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,680
What do you think?

701
00:46:22,720 --> 00:46:23,600
Whatever you decide.

702
00:46:24,520 --> 00:46:26,040
You decide.

703
00:46:36,120 --> 00:46:37,520
So…

704
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:40,080
you really want
to come back and live with us?

705
00:46:41,760 --> 00:46:42,880
Here.

706
00:46:45,600 --> 00:46:47,480
This used to be my room.

707
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:49,520
Can I come back and stay here?

708
00:46:51,680 --> 00:46:53,600
It's a storage room now.

709
00:46:55,600 --> 00:46:56,600
That's fine.

710
00:46:57,480 --> 00:46:58,480
Anywhere is fine

711
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:00,120
as long as

712
00:47:00,800 --> 00:47:03,080
the three of us
can live together as a family,

713
00:47:04,320 --> 00:47:05,920
eat meals together,

714
00:47:06,880 --> 00:47:08,400
laugh together,

715
00:47:10,600 --> 00:47:12,080
sing together again.

716
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,240
And your wife…

717
00:47:19,560 --> 00:47:21,880
Mrs. Mookmanee doesn't mind?

718
00:47:24,680 --> 00:47:26,600
I'll probably have to go
back and forth for now.

719
00:47:28,960 --> 00:47:30,600
I can't quit my job right now.

720
00:47:31,560 --> 00:47:34,760
I really can't find anywhere
that pays as much as Mrs. Mook does.

721
00:47:38,120 --> 00:47:39,120
But

722
00:47:39,680 --> 00:47:41,280
I promise

723
00:47:41,360 --> 00:47:43,560
I'll save up as much money as I can,

724
00:47:44,560 --> 00:47:46,600
so I won't have to depend on her anymore.

725
00:47:48,720 --> 00:47:50,680
I want to live in my own place,

726
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:52,960
to be free,

727
00:47:55,880 --> 00:47:57,240
to be at ease.

728
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,720
And…

729
00:48:01,400 --> 00:48:02,720
to not be looked down on anymore.

730
00:48:32,640 --> 00:48:33,880
What is this meeting?

731
00:48:33,960 --> 00:48:35,440
Why wasn't I informed?

732
00:48:36,040 --> 00:48:39,520
You like surprising other people
but don't like being surprised yourself?

733
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:41,800
What happened?

734
00:48:42,440 --> 00:48:43,560
Nothing much.

735
00:48:43,640 --> 00:48:46,520
Just some evidence.
Do you want me to show it now?

736
00:48:50,640 --> 00:48:51,520
Prarop.

737
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:52,560
Yes, sir.

738
00:49:00,880 --> 00:49:02,080
Everyone, please look.

739
00:49:03,320 --> 00:49:07,080
At 9:58 a.m.,
before we closed the applicant count,

740
00:49:07,160 --> 00:49:08,600
Mr. Trai's team

741
00:49:08,680 --> 00:49:12,120
was ahead of Mr. Rachen's team
by 1,435 applicants.

742
00:49:13,320 --> 00:49:16,040
But at 9:59 a.m.,

743
00:49:16,640 --> 00:49:19,520
Mr. Rachen's team suddenly

744
00:49:19,600 --> 00:49:22,280
gained 3,500 new applicants.

745
00:49:22,360 --> 00:49:23,640
MR. TRAI'S TEAM: 145,900 APPLICANTS
MR. RACHEN'S TEAM: 147,965 APPLICANTS

746
00:49:24,280 --> 00:49:25,240
So what?

747
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:27,440
The numbers could've been delayed.

748
00:49:27,520 --> 00:49:29,440
When the system was about to close,
they might've just popped up.

749
00:49:29,520 --> 00:49:31,040
We checked.

750
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:34,040
Those 3,000 applicants

751
00:49:34,120 --> 00:49:35,360
don't exist.

752
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:37,480
They were fabricated.

753
00:49:38,680 --> 00:49:39,640
Yes.

754
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:43,640
This applicant here, for example,
passed away three years ago.

755
00:49:45,880 --> 00:49:47,720
I had no idea

756
00:49:47,800 --> 00:49:50,760
Be Rich accepted ghosts as customers.

757
00:49:53,640 --> 00:49:54,440
Come here.

758
00:49:57,400 --> 00:49:59,040
Mr. Pittaya, the IT Department head,

759
00:49:59,120 --> 00:50:01,800
already confessed to us
that he was the one who did it.

760
00:50:01,880 --> 00:50:03,080
Why did you do it?

761
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:05,200
Better ask who hired him.

762
00:50:05,280 --> 00:50:06,280
Who was it?

763
00:50:17,480 --> 00:50:19,520
He probably won't answer,
afraid he'll be silenced.

764
00:50:20,640 --> 00:50:23,160
In the end, he'll just say
he did it on his own.

765
00:50:29,400 --> 00:50:32,600
But it's not hard to guess
who's behind it.

766
00:50:36,480 --> 00:50:37,360
I didn't do it.

767
00:50:38,080 --> 00:50:40,480
Yeah. You didn't do it.

768
00:50:40,560 --> 00:50:41,760
Then…

769
00:50:44,080 --> 00:50:45,000
who did?

770
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:53,040
If you think you can stir things up

771
00:50:53,640 --> 00:50:55,200
and turn us against each other,

772
00:50:56,640 --> 00:50:58,080
it won't work, Mr. Trai.

773
00:50:58,880 --> 00:51:00,440
Why would I bother?

774
00:51:01,120 --> 00:51:02,240
That'd be a waste of time.

775
00:51:02,320 --> 00:51:04,840
Because you want the position
so badly that you're literally shaking.

776
00:51:07,080 --> 00:51:07,920
Doesn't look like I'm shaking.

777
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:16,520
What do you want?

778
00:51:24,160 --> 00:51:25,960
You should already know…

779
00:51:29,040 --> 00:51:30,280
what I want.

780
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:46,720
What do you mean?

781
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:49,200
You want me to stay on as Be Rich's CEO?

782
00:51:50,800 --> 00:51:51,640
What game are you playing?

783
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:53,840
Hey, I'm not playing games. I'm serious.

784
00:51:54,440 --> 00:51:58,120
You're more suitable, more capable,
and you know Be Rich better than I do.

785
00:51:59,200 --> 00:52:01,840
And you didn't abandon
the customers from my project either.

786
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:05,200
You knew?

787
00:52:06,720 --> 00:52:08,880
Have you been having people
keep an eye on me?

788
00:52:08,960 --> 00:52:10,840
Come on. Don't call it
keeping an eye on you.

789
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:13,640
Call it watching over you with care.

790
00:52:13,720 --> 00:52:15,600
You're pretending to give me a chance

791
00:52:15,680 --> 00:52:18,400
because you want me to team up
with you against Mrs. Mookmanee?

792
00:52:19,000 --> 00:52:21,840
Don't say "pretending". That sounds fake.

793
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:23,400
I'm sincere.

794
00:52:23,480 --> 00:52:25,160
I really want to work with you.

795
00:52:25,240 --> 00:52:28,040
You've seen it yourself.
Mrs. Mookmanee can do anything.

796
00:52:28,760 --> 00:52:30,800
Faking applicant numbers

797
00:52:30,880 --> 00:52:31,960
is nothing.

798
00:52:32,640 --> 00:52:34,160
She's even manipulated stocks before.

799
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:36,880
- Stocks?
- Yeah.

800
00:52:37,600 --> 00:52:39,520
If you're curious, look into it.
See it with your own eyes.

801
00:52:39,600 --> 00:52:40,560
Then you'll believe me.

802
00:52:41,160 --> 00:52:42,120
I'm going.

803
00:52:43,560 --> 00:52:44,960
I knew Mrs. Mookmanee cheated.

804
00:52:45,040 --> 00:52:46,440
But I didn't object

805
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:49,840
because I wanted that chair.

806
00:52:52,200 --> 00:52:54,440
You love Be Rich, so keep running Be Rich.

807
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:58,000
I'll go do what I love too.

808
00:53:13,480 --> 00:53:16,640
I've upgraded myself
to be ready to be a teacher,

809
00:53:18,520 --> 00:53:20,560
bought children's books,

810
00:53:23,320 --> 00:53:26,040
ordered developmental toys.

811
00:53:27,680 --> 00:53:30,080
You know what we're missing?

812
00:53:31,720 --> 00:53:35,040
Students and teachers.

813
00:53:36,280 --> 00:53:38,680
I already opened online applications,

814
00:53:39,400 --> 00:53:40,360
but it's still quiet.

815
00:53:42,320 --> 00:53:44,440
Then we'll have to go out
and promote it ourselves.

816
00:53:44,520 --> 00:53:46,120
Make killer content,

817
00:53:46,200 --> 00:53:48,560
so people get to know
our alternative school.

818
00:53:48,640 --> 00:53:51,240
I really like that you said "our".

819
00:53:52,560 --> 00:53:55,080
Thank you for taking my dream seriously.

820
00:53:58,520 --> 00:54:00,000
Your dream

821
00:54:00,840 --> 00:54:02,800
is my future too.

822
00:54:03,440 --> 00:54:04,760
Of course I have to take it seriously.

823
00:54:17,720 --> 00:54:19,240
Let me ask you honestly.

824
00:54:19,320 --> 00:54:21,640
Are you enjoying this crazy game?

825
00:54:22,280 --> 00:54:23,760
Tricking people into giving it their all,

826
00:54:23,840 --> 00:54:25,120
and once you've won,

827
00:54:25,200 --> 00:54:26,480
you reject it.

828
00:54:27,960 --> 00:54:30,240
Are you happy
messing with everyone's heads?

829
00:54:31,000 --> 00:54:33,080
You volunteered to help me.

830
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:35,560
So this is my fault?

831
00:54:38,800 --> 00:54:41,640
About the fake applicant numbers,
he already knew about them.

832
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:45,800
That's why he told us to gather evidence
even before you brought it up.

833
00:54:47,360 --> 00:54:48,880
Then why didn't you tell me?

834
00:54:50,280 --> 00:54:51,120
No.

835
00:54:51,200 --> 00:54:53,040
What I should ask is,

836
00:54:53,120 --> 00:54:54,880
when are you ever going to see me?

837
00:54:54,960 --> 00:54:56,840
You say you're sorry for ruining my life,

838
00:54:57,960 --> 00:54:59,880
but you've never cared about me.

839
00:54:59,960 --> 00:55:02,000
You've never once seen my worth.

840
00:55:02,080 --> 00:55:04,840
Da, I understand that you're disappointed.

841
00:55:05,400 --> 00:55:06,960
Go calm down first.

842
00:55:07,040 --> 00:55:08,200
Don't tell me to leave.

843
00:55:14,200 --> 00:55:15,040
Are you happy

844
00:55:15,120 --> 00:55:17,480
now that you've dragged Trai
down to your level?

845
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:18,400
Da.

846
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:22,640
Why would I be happy?

847
00:55:24,160 --> 00:55:25,880
I wanted him to be CEO too.

848
00:55:26,520 --> 00:55:28,960
It's cooler. It looks richer.

849
00:55:29,040 --> 00:55:32,680
I like Mr. Trai as a billionaire
just as much as you do.

850
00:55:34,920 --> 00:55:36,640
But what can I do?

851
00:55:36,720 --> 00:55:38,640
He chose this path

852
00:55:38,720 --> 00:55:41,480
to be the owner of a school
that doesn't have a single student yet.

853
00:55:41,560 --> 00:55:44,080
All I can do is respect his decision,

854
00:55:44,160 --> 00:55:46,360
accept who he is.

855
00:55:46,440 --> 00:55:48,040
It's simple.

856
00:55:48,120 --> 00:55:51,040
But I don't know
if you've ever been able to do that.

857
00:55:54,320 --> 00:55:55,880
He's fooling you too.

858
00:55:56,520 --> 00:55:57,600
He'll say he loves you,

859
00:55:57,680 --> 00:55:59,320
that he'd do anything for you.

860
00:56:00,080 --> 00:56:01,400
But in the end,

861
00:56:01,480 --> 00:56:03,480
you'll just be another one
of his playthings.

862
00:56:04,080 --> 00:56:05,280
Trai has never truly loved anyone.

863
00:56:05,360 --> 00:56:06,920
He only loves himself.

864
00:56:31,920 --> 00:56:33,360
Ms. Darin.

865
00:56:33,880 --> 00:56:35,800
You're hurting yourself.

866
00:56:39,200 --> 00:56:40,520
You saw it, didn't you?

867
00:56:41,880 --> 00:56:44,240
You saw what Trai did to me.

868
00:56:44,320 --> 00:56:45,920
I'm mad at him.

869
00:56:46,440 --> 00:56:47,880
I'm really mad at him.

870
00:56:47,960 --> 00:56:50,640
But even this anger, this hatred,

871
00:56:51,440 --> 00:56:52,680
it's only me.

872
00:56:52,760 --> 00:56:55,120
I'm the only one who feels it.

873
00:56:55,200 --> 00:56:56,480
Why, Rut?

874
00:56:57,280 --> 00:56:59,440
Why am I the only one who gets hurt?

875
00:56:59,960 --> 00:57:02,320
Why has Trai never suffered
the way I have?!

876
00:57:02,400 --> 00:57:03,400
Why?!

877
00:57:08,400 --> 00:57:11,200
I can't take it anymore. I really can't.

878
00:57:16,520 --> 00:57:18,600
Then you don't have to fight anymore.

879
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:20,480
I'll take care of the rest for you.

880
00:57:36,160 --> 00:57:38,520
<i>Are you still thinking about what Da said?</i>

881
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:45,880
No.

882
00:57:46,600 --> 00:57:48,120
Pakbung isn't someone who overthinks.

883
00:57:55,120 --> 00:57:56,600
<i>He's fooling you too.</i>

884
00:57:57,240 --> 00:58:00,080
<i>He'll say he loves you,</i>
<i>that he'd do anything for you.</i>

885
00:58:00,840 --> 00:58:02,160
But in the end,

886
00:58:02,240 --> 00:58:04,560
you'll just be another one
of his playthings.

887
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:07,760
Trai has never truly loved anyone.

888
00:58:07,840 --> 00:58:09,000
He only loves himself.

889
00:58:15,880 --> 00:58:16,920
<i>Good night.</i>

890
00:58:26,120 --> 00:58:27,680
Only loves himself?

891
00:58:32,600 --> 00:58:34,040
Why don't we try dating, Mr. Trai?

892
00:58:35,240 --> 00:58:36,960
You asked Mr. Trai to be your boyfriend?!

893
00:58:38,120 --> 00:58:39,960
I give myself to you.

894
00:58:40,040 --> 00:58:42,320
Then I'll be your gift too.

895
00:58:46,120 --> 00:58:48,240
You and I should sleep
in Dad's room together.

896
00:58:48,320 --> 00:58:49,560
I already have someone taking care of me.

897
00:58:49,640 --> 00:58:51,440
I'm coming.

898
00:58:51,520 --> 00:58:53,080
- Pakbung?
- Trai told me

899
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:54,560
he won't take anything from me again.

900
00:58:54,640 --> 00:58:56,040
<i>That probably includes you too.</i>

901
00:58:56,120 --> 00:58:58,320
If Rachen joins forces with his brother,

902
00:58:58,400 --> 00:59:00,080
that means he wants to be my enemy.

903
00:59:00,160 --> 00:59:02,200
What should be done with a traitor?

904
00:59:02,280 --> 00:59:04,640
<i>Stop dumping all the blame on him alone.</i>

905
00:59:04,720 --> 00:59:06,760
Share some of that guilt too.

906
00:59:06,840 --> 00:59:08,200
I want her to suffer.

907
00:59:08,280 --> 00:59:09,920
It'd be even better if she just died.

908
00:59:11,120 --> 00:59:13,000
I won't let myself get caught,

909
00:59:13,080 --> 00:59:15,080
not until I see the end of all of you.

910
00:59:21,640 --> 00:59:22,520
Rachen!

911
01:00:10,520 --> 01:00:12,520
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
